 Co-integration test results 
 
 The formal analysis is done in a vector autoregressive (VAR) (solid basic structure on which bigger things can be built) to use (for selfish reasons) properties 
 of (combination of different things together that work as one unit) and co-integration that may exist in the 
 data. VAR methods offer a easily-controlled (solid basic structure on which bigger things can be built) for the 
 (act of asking questions and trying to find the truth about something) of energetic relations, especially when 
 the (numbers that change/things that change) are co-integrated. Think about/believe a VAR(k) 
